textRuns.value: Between 2019 and 2021 an average of 58% of service users were male and 41% were homeless. In 2020 there was a slight increase in female and housed service users, perhaps due to Covid-19.
Australians, Aborigines and Torres Strait Islanders account for over 90% of service users. The percentage from outside Australia has decreased from 6.45% in 2019 to 3.78% in 2021.
Between 2019 and 2021 the percentage of people over 65 requiring services has nearly doubled from 5.87% to 10.34%. At the same time the percentage of service users under 17 has fallen to 0%.
